article.headline: Alabama St. 35, Grambling St. 16
article.story: GRAMBLING, La. (AP) -- Alabama State quarterback Alex Engram scored twice and running back Jay Peck rushed for just under 100 yards in the Hornets' 35-16 Southwestern Athletic Conference win Saturday over Grambling State. Grambling (3-6, 3-4 SWAC) went into the half ahead 16-13 but it was all Alabama State (4-5, 4-4) in the second half which saw the Hornets reel off 22 unanswered points. During a fourth-down play on Grambling's opening drive, Tim Manuel lost control of the ball after a botched punt attempt and Alabama State's Justin Wright recovered the fumble for a 15-yard score to move the Hornets ahead 19-16. Two possessions later, Grambling's Ruben Mayes fumbled on his own 1-yard line and the Hornets upped their lead to 25-16 when Engram scored on a quarterback keeper at the 6:54 mark of the quarter. After two drives late in the fourth that featured an interception and a series that saw the Tigers fail to convert a 4th-and-20 on their own 10, Rahmond Taylor scored for Alabama State at the 3:34 mark from 20 yards out to seal the win. Grambling, which hadn't lost to ASU since 1999, netted a season low 207 yards of total offense, compared to Alabama State's 225. Peck led the Hornets on offense with 97 yards on 24 carries. Engram completed just 3 of 13 passes for 43 yards but added 36 on the ground, including two rushing touchdowns. Grambling starter Brandon Landers threw for 104 yards on 11-of-27 passing with one interception in the homecoming loss. Backup quarterback Larry Kerlegan, who also saw some action, was 2-of-3 for 71 yards.
